{{page-title "Documentation — Scores"}}
<div class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl py-6 px-4 space-y-6">

  <Panel::Card>
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">Scores</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-600">
      A Score is an AI-generated assessment of how well your professional
      profile matches a specific job posting. It gives you a numeric rating
      (0–100) and a written explanation of your strengths and gaps. Run it
      before you invest time in a cover letter or application.
    </p>
    {{! <img src="" alt="screenshot of a score detail page showing the numeric score and explanation" /> }}
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">How Scoring Works</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mb-3">
      From a Job Post detail page, click "Generate Score." The AI receives the
      job description and your Career Data and evaluates:
    </p>
    <ul class="text-gray-600 text-sm list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
      <li>Technical skill overlap between the job requirements and your
        background</li>
      <li>Experience level and seniority alignment</li>
      <li>Industry and domain familiarity</li>
      <li>Specific requirements mentioned in the job description</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-600 mt-3">
      The result includes a numeric score and a paragraph explaining what
      matched and what didn't. The gaps section is often the most useful part.
    </p>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Interpreting a Score</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-sm">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span
          class="bg-green-100 text-green-700 px-2 py-0.5 rounded font-semibold shrink-0"
        >80–100</span>
        <p class="text-gray-600">Strong match. Apply with confidence. The cover
          letter will need minimal customization.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span
          class="bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-700 px-2 py-0.5 rounded font-semibold shrink-0"
        >60–79</span>
        <p class="text-gray-600">Reasonable fit with some gaps. Worth applying
          if the role interests you — address the gaps in your cover letter.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
        <span
          class="bg-red-100 text-red-700 px-2 py-0.5 rounded font-semibold shrink-0"
        >Below 60</span>
        <p class="text-gray-600">Significant mismatch. Either the role is a
          stretch, or your Career Data doesn't yet reflect relevant experience
          you have.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-4">
      Note: a low score isn't necessarily a veto — it might mean your Career
      Data needs updating. If you have the experience but scored poorly, review
      your Career Data and regenerate.
    </p>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Using Scores
      Strategically</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 text-sm list-disc list-inside">
      <li>Run a score before writing a cover letter — it tells you what to
        emphasize</li>
      <li>Use the gap analysis to improve your Career Data for better future
        scores</li>
      <li>Prioritize applications where you score highly — your time is finite</li>
      <li>Compare scores across similar roles to understand where you're most
        competitive</li>
    </ul>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Example Score</h2>
    <div
      class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded p-4 text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-3"
    >
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
        <span class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-600">87</span>
        <span class="text-gray-400 text-lg">/ 100</span>
        <span
          class="bg-green-100 text-green-700 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs font-semibold"
        >Strong match</span>
      </div>
      <p>
        Strong alignment with the backend requirements. Your Python and Django
        experience maps directly to the tech stack, and your work on
        high-traffic APIs at Meridian Health is relevant to the scalability
        concerns mentioned in the description.
      </p>
      <p>
        The job emphasizes Kubernetes orchestration, which is not reflected in
        your Career Data. Your Docker and Docker Swarm experience is related but
        not equivalent — consider adding this to Career Data if you have any
        Kubernetes exposure, even in side projects or training. The Ember.js
        frontend requirement is a secondary concern; your experience is on the
        backend, and the role's primary focus appears to be there as well.
      </p>
    </div>
    {{! <img src="" alt="screenshot of this score in the show view" /> }}
  </Panel::Card>

</div>